        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 16 at 6:18PM CDT by NWS Kansas City/Pleasant Hill MO</headline>
        <description>At 618 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Mission Hills. This thunderstorm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Kansas City, Raytown, Prairie Village, Mission Hills, Westwood,
Westwood Hills, and Mission Woods.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 70 in Missouri near mile marker 7.
Interstate 435 between mile markers 63 and 69.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
